Package au.edu.anu.twcore.experiment.runtime

Interface DataLoader<T extends fr.cnrs.iees.properties.SimplePropertyList>

All Known Implementing Classes:
PropertyDataLoader
public interface DataLoader<T extends fr.cnrs.iees.properties.SimplePropertyList>

A DataLoader is a class that loads data from a single source (usually a StringList) into a single 3Worlds data storage object of the SimplePropertyList class. The data source is usually a chunk of a file extracted by a MultipleDataLoader. In other words:

1 file chunk <--> 1 DataLoader <---> 1 SimplePropertyList (actually TwData)

A new DataLoader class should be defined for any new file format used to input data into 3Worlds. The descendant class must link to the data source in its constructor. The class is meant to be used with a MultipleDataLoader. cf as an implementation example CsvDataLoader.

The T parameter defines the return type of the load() method - in 3Worlds it is usually TwData, but any other implementation of SimplePropertyList could be used. This means it is possible to use for example the CsvDataLoader to load node properties from a csv file.
